tables.table_schema:
CREATE TABLE transactions (
   transaction_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
   item_id INT,
   supplier_id INT,
   transaction_date TIMESTAMP,
   quantity INT
);

CREATE TABLE suppliers (
  id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  supplier_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
  contact_number VARCHAR(20) NOT NULL,
  email VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
  address VARCHAR(255)
);

CREATE TABLE supply_orders (
  id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  supplier_id INT NOT NULL,
  item_id INT NOT NULL,
  quantity_ordered INT NOT NULL,
  order_date DATE
);

CREATE TABLE Supplier (
    supplier_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    supplier_name VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    contact_person VARCHAR(50),
    phone_number VARCHAR(15),
    email VARCHAR(50)
);

CREATE TABLE SupplyChain (
    chain_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    supplier_id INT NOT NULL,
    location_id INT NOT NULL,
    supply_date DATE,
    FOREIGN KEY (supplier_id) REFERENCES Supplier(supplier_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (location_id) REFERENCES InventoryLocation(location_id)
);

CREATE TABLE ReplenishmentHistory (
    replenish_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    supply_id INT NOT NULL,
    replenish_date DATE,
    quantity_added INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (supply_id) REFERENCES MedicalSupplies(id)
);
